# Frontend Rules

## Folder Layout
src/
  main.tsx                    # Entry point
  App.tsx                     # Root component and routing
  pages/                      # One file per route
    CustomerChat.tsx           # Route: /
    ManagerDashboard.tsx       # Route: /manager
  components/                 # Feature-specific reusable components
    ui/                       # Generic stateless UI primitives only
    generative/               # Generative UI components
      CardStatusWidget.tsx
      TransactionStatusWidget.tsx
  context/                    # React Context providers
    BotConfigContext.tsx
    MistakesContext.tsx
    AuthContext.tsx
  api/                        # All fetch calls to backend, never inline
    botApi.ts
    configApi.ts
    mistakesApi.ts
    metaAgentApi.ts
  hooks/                      # Custom React hooks
  utils/                      # Pure helper functions, no React imports
  types/                      # Shared TypeScript types and interfaces
  assets/                     # Static assets

## Naming Conventions
- Pages and components: PascalCase (CustomerChat.tsx, ChatBubble.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase prefixed with use (useAuth.ts, useChatStream.ts)
- Utils: camelCase (formatDate.ts, parseGeminiResponse.ts)
- Types: PascalCase (MistakeTypes.ts, BotConfigTypes.ts)
- API files: camelCase suffixed with Api (botApi.ts, mistakesApi.ts)

## Folder Rules
- pages/ — one file per route only, no business logic
- components/ui/ — only generic context-free primitives, no business logic
- components/ — feature components that use ui/ primitives and hooks
- hooks/ — must be prefixed with use
- utils/ — pure functions only, no React imports ever
- api/ — all fetch calls live here only, never inline in components

## Routing
- React Router v6
- / → CustomerChat.tsx (public)
- /manager → ManagerDashboard.tsx (password gated)
- Hardcoded password: "atome2024"

## State Management
- React Context only. No Redux, no Zustand
- Three contexts: BotConfigContext, MistakesContext, AuthContext
- All contexts live in src/context/

## API Layer
- All fetch calls in src/api/ only, never inline in components
- Always handle loading and error states
- Backend base URL from environment variable VITE_API_URL

## TypeScript
- Never use any or unknown without a comment explaining why
- All API response shapes must have a defined type in src/types/
- All props must be typed

## Generative UI
- Bot responses return either plain text or structured JSON
- Always check if response is valid JSON first, fall back to plain text
- CardStatusWidget.tsx renders card application status
- TransactionStatusWidget.tsx renders transaction details

## Design
- Atome primary: #F4FF5F
- Contrast: #000000
- Background: #FFFFFF, panels: #F9F9F9
- Border radius: rounded-xl (12px)
- Use shadcn/ui and HeroUI before raw Tailwind
- Bot bubbles: black background, white text, left aligned
- Customer bubbles: #F4FF5F background, black text, right aligned
- Streaming responses must show typing indicator while streaming